.TH "madmail" "1" "2026-06-11" "2.4.0" "User Commands"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
madmail - Chatmail mail server and operator CLI
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBmadmail\fR [\fBoptions\fR]
.PP
\fBmadmail\fR \fBrun\fR [\fBoptions\fR]
.PP
\fBmadmail\fR \fBcommand\fR [\fBsubcommand\fR] [\fBoptions\fR] [\fBarguments\fR.\&.\&.\&]
.PP
Common forms:
.PP
\fBmadmail\fR [\fB--config\fR \fIfile\fR] [\fB--state-dir\fR \fIdir\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.PP
\fBmadmail\fR \fBinstall\fR \fB--simple\fR \fB--ip\fR \fIaddress\fR [\fIoptions\fR.\&.\&.\&]
.PP
\fBmadmail\fR \fBaccounts\fR \fBstatus\fR
.PP
\fBmadmail\fR \fBadmin-token\fR [\fB--raw\fR]
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fBmadmail\fR is a single executable that runs a Chatmail mail server (SMTP,
submission, IMAP, HTTP registration UI, admin API) and provides operator
commands compatible with the Madmail and maddy CLIs.\&
.PP
Invoking \fBmadmail\fR with no subcommand is equivalent to \fBmadmail run\fR and
starts network services defined in the configuration file.\&
.PP
Operator subcommands open the configuration and state databases directly
or call the admin API.\&
They are intended for installation, monitoring, and day-to-day
administration on the host where the server runs.\&
.PP
The executable basename (for example \fBmadmail\fR or \fBchatmail\fR) is taken
from \fBargv[0]\fR.\&
It determines default config and state paths, the systemd unit name, the
service user name, and installed man/completion file names when using
\fBinstall\fR.\&
.PP
Extended documentation:
<https://github.\&com/themadorg/madmail/tree/main/docs/guide/cli>
.PP
.SS Server mode
.PP
\fBrun\fR
.RS 4
Start SMTP, submission, IMAP, HTTP, and related endpoints.\&
Read configuration from \fB--config\fR and persistent state from
\fB--state-dir\fR (alias \fB--libexec\fR).\&
.PP
.RE
.SS Installation and lifecycle
.PP
\fBinstall\fR
.RS 4
Write configuration, TLS material, databases, optional systemd unit,
service user, system-wide binary, manual page, and shell tab
completion scripts.\&
See EXAMPLES and NOTES.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBuninstall\fR
.RS 4
Remove the service, configuration, and data.\&
Confirmation is required; use keep flags such as \fB--keep-data\fR to
preserve selected artifacts.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBupgrade\fR, \fBupdate\fR
.RS 4
Replace this executable from a signed local file or URL.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBreload\fR
.RS 4
Apply database configuration overrides and restart via the admin API.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBversion\fR
.RS 4
Print package version and exit.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBstatus\fR
.RS 4
Show server status (connections, registered users, uptime).\&
.PP
.RE
.SS Accounts and access
.PP
\fBaccounts\fR
.RS 4
Account management: \fBstatus\fR, \fBinfo\fR, \fBcreate\fR, \fBcreate-random\fR,
\fBdelete\fR, \fBban\fR, \fBunban\fR, \fBexport\fR, \fBimport\fR, \fBdelete-all\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBban-list\fR
.RS 4
List blocklisted usernames (alias for \fBaccounts ban-list\fR).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBblocklist\fR
.RS 4
Manage usernames blocked from re-registration.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBcreate-user\fR
.RS 4
Create a random account and print JSON credentials.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBdelete\fR
.RS 4
Fully delete a user (credentials, mail, blocklist entry).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBadmin-token\fR
.RS 4
Display admin API credentials (optional login QR code).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBadmin-web\fR
.RS 4
Enable, disable, or configure the embedded admin web dashboard.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBregistration\fR
.RS 4
Open or close public account registration.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBregistration-tokens\fR (\fBreg-tokens\fR, \fBtokens\fR)
.RS 4
Manage invite tokens for account creation.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS Mail policy and delivery
.PP
\fBfederation\fR
.RS 4
Federation policy, domain rules, and silent-dismiss lists.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBendpoint-cache\fR (\fBdns-cache\fR)
.RS 4
Outbound delivery DNS override cache.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBsharing\fR
.RS 4
Delta Chat contact share links.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBmessage-size\fR
.RS 4
View or set maximum message size limits.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBtasks\fR
.RS 4
Scheduled maintenance jobs (message retention, unused accounts, queue
purge).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBqueue\fR
.RS 4
Delivery queue management.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS Network and TLS
.PP
\fBport\fR
.RS 4
Admin-panel listener ports and local/public bind mode.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBcertificate\fR
.RS 4
TLS certificates (Let'\&s Encrypt autocert, file, self-signed).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBsubmission-access\fR
.RS 4
SMTP submission access scope (public or local).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBpush\fR
.RS 4
Delta Chat push notification mode (\fBauto\fR, \fBon\fR, \fBoff\fR).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBwebimap\fR, \fBwebsmtp\fR
.RS 4
Enable or disable WebIMAP and WebSMTP HTTP APIs.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS Customization
.PP
\fBlanguage\fR
.RS 4
Website language (\fBen\fR, \fBfa\fR, \fBru\fR, \fBes\fR).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBhtml-export\fR
.RS 4
Export default HTML/CSS assets to a directory.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBhtml-serve\fR
.RS 4
Serve the web UI from an external directory (\fBembedded\fR reverts to
built-in files).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBhash\fR
.RS 4
Generate password hashes for \fBpass_table\fR configuration.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS Shell documentation helpers
.PP
\fBcompletion\fR \fBbash\fR|\fBzsh\fR|\fBfish\fR
.RS 4
Print a tab-completion script to stdout.\&
.PP
.RE
Hidden packager helpers (not shown in default help):
\fBgenerate-man\fR, \fBgenerate-fish-completion\fR.\&
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
The following options are accepted before every subcommand.\&
.PP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
.RS 4
Print a short usage summary and exit.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB--config\fR \fIfile\fR
.RS 4
Configuration file path.\&
Overrides the built-in default when set.\&
Environment variable: \fBCHATMAIL_CONFIG\fR.\&
Default: \fI/etc/madmail/madmail.\&conf\fR (or a development default when
that file is absent).\&
.PP
.RE
\fB--state-dir\fR \fIdir\fR, \fB--libexec\fR \fIdir\fR
.RS 4
Persistent state directory (databases, mail storage, ACME state,
queues).\&
Environment variable: \fBCHATMAIL_STATE_DIR\fR.\&
Default: \fI/var/lib/madmail\fR (or a development default under the
current working directory).\&
.PP
.RE
\fB--json\fR
.RS 4
Emit machine-readable JSON on standard output for operator
subcommands.\&
Suppresses decorative text and QR codes.\&
On failure, a JSON error object is written to standard error and the
exit status is non-zero.\&
.PP
.RE
Subcommands accept additional options documented in \fBmadmail command
--help\fR and in the online CLI reference.\&
.PP
.SH EXIT STATUS
.PP
\fB0\fR
.RS 4
Success.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB1\fR
.RS 4
General error (configuration, I/O, validation, or remote admin API
failure).\&
An explanatory message is printed to standard error.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.PP
\fBCHATMAIL_CONFIG\fR
.RS 4
Default configuration file path.\&
See \fB--config\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBCHATMAIL_STATE_DIR\fR
.RS 4
Default state directory.\&
See \fB--state-dir\fR and \fB--libexec\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH FILES
.PP
\fI/etc/madmail/madmail.\&conf\fR
.RS 4
Default main configuration file after system install (actual name is
/etc/madmail/BINARY.\&conf where BINARY is the executable basename).\&
.PP
.RE
\fI/etc/madmail/certs/\fR
.RS 4
Default TLS certificate and private key directory after install.\&
.PP
.RE
\fI/var/lib/madmail/\fR
.RS 4
Default state directory after system install (actual path uses the
executable basename).\&
.PP
.RE
\fI/usr/local/bin/madmail\fR
.RS 4
Default destination for the binary on system install.\&
.PP
.RE
\fI/usr/share/man/man1/madmail.\&1\fR
.RS 4
Manual page installed by \fBmadmail install\fR on system installs.\&
.PP
.RE
\fI/usr/share/bash-completion/completions/madmail\fR
.RS 4
Bash tab completion installed by \fBmadmail install\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
Zsh tab completion is installed under /usr/share/zsh/site-functions/ using
the executable basename prefixed by an underscore (for example
\fI/usr/share/zsh/site-functions/madmail\fR when the binary is \fBmadmail\fR).\&
Installed by \fBmadmail install\fR.\&
.PP
\fI/usr/share/fish/vendor_completions.\&d/madmail.\&fish\fR
.RS 4
Fish tab completion installed by \fBmadmail install\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
\fI/etc/systemd/system/madmail.\&service\fR
.RS 4
Default systemd unit path after system install.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Simple install on a public IPv4 address (self-signed TLS by default):
.PP
.RS 4
sudo madmail install --simple --ip 203.\&0.\&113.\&50 --lang en
.PP
.RE
Install on a DNS hostname with Let'\&s Encrypt (port 80 must be free during
install when certificate issuance runs):
.PP
.RS 4
sudo madmail install --simple --domain mail.\&example.\&org --acme-email admin@example.\&org --lang en
.PP
.RE
Preview a system install without writing files:
.PP
.RS 4
sudo madmail install --simple --ip 203.\&0.\&113.\&50 --dry-run
.PP
.RE
Start the server under systemd after install:
.PP
.RS 4
sudo systemctl enable --now madmail
journalctl -u madmail -n 100 --no-pager
.PP
.RE
Start manually with explicit paths (local or development layout):
.PP
.RS 4
madmail --config /etc/madmail/madmail.\&conf run --libexec /var/lib/madmail
.PP
.RE
Show account summary as JSON for scripting:
.PP
.RS 4
madmail --json accounts status
.PP
.RE
Print admin API token for scripts:
.PP
.RS 4
TOKEN=$(madmail admin-token --raw --no-qr)
.PP
.RE
Install bash completion without a full system install:
.PP
.RS 4
madmail completion bash | sudo tee /usr/share/bash-completion/completions/madmail
.PP
.RE
.SH NOTES
.PP
\fBinstall\fR requires root for system installs (service user, binary copy,
systemd unit, man page, and completions).\&
Use explicit non-FHS \fB--config-dir\fR and \fB--state-dir\fR for local
installs that skip those steps.\&
.PP
Interactive \fBinstall\fR (without \fB--simple\fR or \fB--non-interactive\fR) may
not be available in all builds; use \fB--simple\fR or \fB--non-interactive\fR
in scripts.\&
.PP
When \fB--json\fR is set, successful operator commands print a single JSON
object on standard output.\&
See the online JSON schema guide in the repository docs/guide/cli/
directory.\&
.PP
.SH CAVEATS
.PP
TLS with a public IP relay often uses self-signed certificates or
\fBturn_off_tls\fR unless \fB--auto-ip-cert\fR and a valid ACME contact email
are supplied.\&
Delta Chat clients may need to accept self-signed certificates on such
relays.\&
.PP
Replacing the running binary in place while the server is active is
unsafe.\&
Use \fBupgrade\fR or stop the service before overwriting the executable.\&
.PP
.SH BUGS
.PP
Report issues at
<https://github.\&com/themadorg/madmail/issues>.\&
.PP
